                    <h1 class="flex justify-center blog-heding">How to Connect USB Devices to Your Mobile Phone</h1>
                </div>
                <div class="overview margin-bottom">
                    <p class="blog-text-overview margin-bottom">In today's tech-savvy world, mobile phones have evolved
                        into powerful devices capable of performing various tasks beyond making calls and sending texts.
                        One useful feature is the ability to connect USB devices, expanding the functionality and
                        usability of your smartphone. Whether you want to transfer files, connect external storage, or
                        use peripherals like keyboards or game controllers, understanding how to connect USB devices to
                        your mobile phone is essential. In this guide, we'll explore the step-by-step process and
                        explain it clearly for users of all levels.</p>
                </div>

                <hr>
                <section class="container margin-top">
                    <div class="blog-step-1 margin-bottom">
                        <h1 class="margin-bottom"> Check USB OTG Compatibility:</h1>
                        <p class="blog-text-overview margin-top-bottom">Before attempting to connect a USB device to
                            your mobile phone, ensure that your device supports USB On-The-Go (OTG) functionality. Most
                            modern Android smartphones and tablets support OTG, allowing them to act as hosts for USB
                            devices. You can verify your device's compatibility by checking the specifications on the
                            manufacturer's website or consulting the user manual.</p>
                    </div>
                    <hr>
                    <div class="blog-step-2 margin-top-bottom">
                        <h1 class="margin-bottom">Obtain a USB OTG Adapter:</h1>
                        <p class="blog-text-overview margin-top-bottom">To connect USB devices to your mobile phone,
                            you'll need a USB OTG adapter. This small adapter features a micro USB or USB-C connector on
                            one end and a standard USB port on the other. You can purchase USB OTG adapters from
                            electronics stores or online retailers at affordable prices.</p>
